<title>SINGAPORE: Stamford acquires U.S. unit.</title>
<headline>Stamford acquires U.S. unit.</headline>
<dateline>SINGAPORE 1996-08-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Stamford Tyres Corp Ltd said on Thursday it had bought the entire equity in STC Tires (USA)) Inc (STC-USA), a private limited company incorporated in Miami, Florida.</p>
<p>The authorised, issued and paid up capital of STC-USA is US$10,000, made up of 10,000 ordinary shares of US$1 par value each.</p>
<p>It said it had bought STC-USA for the purpose of setting up a tyre distribution centre in Miami that would provide easy access to the Carribean Islands, South and Central America.</p>
<p>The Miami presence will also give the Group opportunities to source for tyres for group distribution from North America and to sell the in-house brand of tyres there.</p>
<p>-Singapore newsroom (65-8703080)</p>
